definitions.definition: A larva , in a stage following the zoea , in the development of most crabs . In this stage the legs and abdominal appendages have appeared, the abdomen is relatively long, and the eyes are large.
A large fish of the genus Megalops .

main_definition: ( zoology ) A larva , in a stage following the zoea , in the development of most crabs . In this stage the legs and abdominal appendages have appeared, the abdomen is relatively long, and the eyes are large.
